snippet: Andy Murray believes he will probably have to wait until next year to reach the world number one spot at the expense of Novak Djokovic as the two are on a final collision course at the Paris Masters....
lead_paragraph: Andy Murray believes he will probably have to wait until next year to reach the world number one spot at the expense of Novak Djokovic as the two are on a final collision course at the Paris Masters.

headline.print_headline: Top Ranking May Have to Wait Until Next Year, Says Murray
headline.main: Top Ranking May Have to Wait Until Next Year, Says Murray
